This paper involves both machine learning and information retrieval, which are covered by several sub-categories in arXiv CS. The most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), as the paper proposes a joint learning algorithm for sparse coding and ranking score learning. The second likely sub-category is cs.IR (Information Retrieval), as the paper addresses the problem of learning ranking scores from data points. The third likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision), as sparse coding is a popular method for image processing and computer vision tasks. The fourth likely sub-category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), as the paper involves learning algorithms and optimization techniques. The fifth likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), as the paper may involve natural language processing tasks that require sparse coding and ranking.
